message:
From INTERPOL HQ Nearly 350 victims of human trafficking rescued in Interpol raids throughout Latin America and the Caribbean.
Police arrested 22 individuals during Operation Libertad raids, carried out between April 3-9, which marked the culmination of the Canadian government-funded two-and-a-half-year effort, Interpol said.
#interpol #humantrafficking #internationalpolice #leo #caribbean #slavery
